user_input:
I would like to extend the roles and add a way to define input type (prompts, md file located under document folder, json) and output (md file, json, llm repsonse,  github code..)
Also I would like to add to 2 reviewr roles using statefull (accumulates history) and stateless where stateless, fresh reviewer — no accumulated context from prior rounds (no memroy, fresh context every call)
Each agent node can show its input/output IO tags colour-coded by type (purple = prompt, blue = md file, green = code/github, amber = tests/report, red = feedback, teal = score/json). 
All workflow will be configured behind as Yaml file that will have addiotanl configuration such retry, max attempt, threshhold...
The goal is to be able to build simple workflow that can be full automated or semi-autoamated as they will stop from asking user question or ending by user requests.. all workflows will use langgraph behind the hood to run the full pipeline 
Documents outputs will be under Document folder and code output will be to GitHub. 
There is a simple html as UI sample below , you can adjust that to the current UI: 

<!DOCTYPE html>
